Package org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry

Class SizeD

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.SizeD

  • public final class SizeD
extends Object
    Represents an extension in two-dimensional space, using Double coordinates. SizeD contains two immutable non-negative Double extensions. Use SizeI to represent sizes with Integer extensions.
    Version:
    6.0.0
    Author:
    Christoph Nahr

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public SizeD add​(SizeD size)
        Adds the extension of the specified SizeD to this instance. Returns Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY in any dimension that overflows Double.
        Parameters:
        size - the SizeD whose extension to add to this instance
        Returns:
        a SizeD whose width and height equal the addition of the corresponding dimensions of the specified size to this instance
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if size is null

      • equals

        public static boolean equals​(SizeD a,
                             SizeD b,
                             double epsilon)
        Compares two SizeD instances for equality, given the specified epsilon.
        Parameters:
        a - the first SizeD to compare
        b - the second SizeD to compare
        epsilon - the maximum absolute difference where the corresponding dimensions of a and b are considered equal
        Returns:
        true if the absolute difference between both corresponding dimensions of a and b is no greater than epsilon, else false
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if epsilon is less than zero
        NullPointerException - if a or b is null

      • fromDoubles

        public static SizeD[] fromDoubles​(double... sizes)
        Converts the specified Double array to a SizeD array. The returned array has half as many elements as the specified sizes and retains the same dimension sequence.
        Parameters:
        sizes - an array containing the width and height components of SizeD instances, stored in alternating index positions
        Returns:
        the SizeD array created from sizes
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if sizes has an odd number of elements, or if any width or height is less than zero
        NullPointerException - if sizes is null

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty​()
        Determines whether the SizeD is empty.
        Returns:
        true if both width and height equal zero, else false

      • restrict

        public SizeD restrict​(double minWidth,
                      double minHeight,
                      double maxWidth,
                      double maxHeight)
        Restricts the SizeD to the specified extension range.
        Parameters:
        minWidth - the smallest permissible width
        minHeight - the smallest permissible height
        maxWidth - the greatest permissible width
        maxHeight - the greatest permissible height
        Returns:
        a SizeD whose width and height equal those of this instance, restricted to the specified extension range
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if maxWidth or maxHeight is less than zero

      • round

        public SizeI round​()
        Converts the SizeD to a SizeI by rounding dimensions to the nearest Integer values. Uses Fortran.nint(double) for rounding.
        Returns:
        a SizeI whose SizeI.width and SizeI.height equal the corresponding dimensions of the SizeD, rounded to the nearest Integer values
        Throws:
        ArithmeticException - if any dimension overflows Integer

      • subtract

        public SizeD subtract​(SizeD size)
        Subtracts the extension of the specified SizeD from this instance.
        Parameters:
        size - the SizeD extension to subtract from this instance
        Returns:
        a SizeD whose width and height equal the subtraction of the corresponding dimensions of the specified size from this instance
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the difference in any dimension is less than zero
        NullPointerException - if size is null

      • toDoubles

        public static double[] toDoubles​(SizeD... sizes)
        Converts the specified SizeD array to a Double array. The returned array has twice as many elements as the specified sizes and retains the same dimension sequence.
        Parameters:
        sizes - the SizeD array to convert
        Returns:
        an array containing the width and height components of all sizes, stored in alternating index positions
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if sizes or any of its elements is null

      • toSizeI

        public SizeI toSizeI​()
        Converts the SizeD to a SizeI by truncating dimensions to the nearest Integer values. Uses Integer casts for truncation.
        Returns:
        a SizeI whose SizeI.width and SizeI.height equal the corresponding dimensions of the SizeD, truncated to the nearest Integer values
        Throws:
        ArithmeticException - if any dimension overflows Integer
